plants.name: cactus
plants.description: A cactus is a type of succulent plant known for its thick, fleshy stems, often with spines or thorns, adapted to store water in arid climates.

plants.name: hibiscus
plants.description: Hibiscus is a genus of flowering plants known for their large, colorful blooms. These plants are often found in warm temperate, subtropical, and tropical regions and are commonly used in gardens and landscapes for their ornamental beauty.

plants.name: Maize Plant
plants.description: Maize, also known as corn in North American and Australian English, is a tall stout grass that produces cereal grain. It was domesticated by indigenous peoples in southern Mexico about 9,000 years ago from wild teosinte. Native Americans planted it alongside beans and squashes in the Three Sisters polyculture.

plants.name: Pink Rose
plants.description: Pink roses typically symbolise admiration, happiness, and love. More subtle than the traditional bold red rose, pink roses are often used to signify a strong friendship or the love between family members.

plants.name: Mango Plant
plants.description: Mangifera indica, commonly known as mango, is a species of flowering plant in the family Anacardiaceae. It is a large fruit tree, capable of growing to a height of 30 metres. There are two distinct genetic populations in modern mangoes – the "Indian type" and the "Southeast Asian type"
